%TUTORIAL -`-`- ZIL - RELINK FUNCTION INTO PROGRAM -`-`- TUTORIAL
%SELECTION ===>_ZCMD                                                           +
+
     Use this option to relink a recompiled ZIL function into a compiled
     ZIL program, without having to recompile the entire program.

     The compiled@function+load module specified by\FUNCTION NAME+will be
     included from the library specified by\INCLUDED FROM LIBRARY+when
     the compiled@program+load module specified by\MAIN PROGRAM NAME+is
     relinked in the load library specified by\LOAD MODULE LIBRARY.+

    @Do not+specify a function name as the main program name.  Doing it
     would prevent you from being able to access the correct versions of
     functions under the interpreter.

     The load library must already contain the program which is to be
     relinked using the new version of the function.  If it does not,
     you may copy in the program via ISPF option#3.3.

)INIT
)PROC
)END
